<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="136" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="29.[432,1831,626,931]" pageId="29" pageNumber="136">The genus may be characterized briefly as follows: Head usually nearly as broad as the pronotum; crown short and broad; face short and broad with the ocelli well below the level of the dorsal margin. Pronotum short and broad; the anterior margin not projecting in front of the anterior margin of the compound eyes. Mesonotum short, broadly triangular. Tegmina translucent; venation indistinct.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[433,1832,982,1230]" pageId="29" pageNumber="136">
This is a genus of about 90 species of world-wide distribution. Osborn (21) described four new species from 
<collectingCountry box="[1138,1255,1035,1078]" name="Samoa" pageId="29" pageNumber="136">Samoa</collectingCountry>
and listed a fifth species, previously recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[814,937,1086,1129]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="29" pageNumber="136">Ceylon</collectingCountry>
, for this region. Only one other species has been recorded from Pacific islands, and no species have heretofore been recorded frbm 
<collectingCountry box="[537,735,1190,1230]" name="Micronesia" pageId="29" pageNumber="136">Micronesia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
